articles.description: Amanze Egekeze poured in 28 points, including a go-ahead 3-pointer with 60 seconds left in the game, to propel Belmont to a 75-70 victory over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Egekeze lifts Belmont to 75-70 win over Tennessee Tech

articles.description: Colorado State suspended interim head coach Steve Barnes just hours before Saturday's Mountain West game and assistant coach Jase Herl took his place, helping the team snap a seven-game losing streak with a 90-79 win over San Jose State.
articles.headline: Interim coach Steve Barnes suspended before game; assistant Jase Herl guides Rams to victory

articles.description: Chris Cokley had 15 points and nine rebounds and UAB rallied from nine down with less than four minutes to go for a 61-56 win on Saturday night.
articles.headline: UAB rallies past Rice 61-56

articles.description: The Tigers take down the Bulldogs 78-61 to earn their first sweep since the 1985-86 season.
articles.headline: No. 8 Auburn sweeps UGA in regular season

images.caption: The Tigers take down the Bulldogs 78-61 to earn their first sweep since the 1985-86 season.
images.name: No. 8 Auburn sweeps UGA in regular season

articles.description: Shakur Juiston scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and UNLV beat Wyoming 85-70 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Juiston leads UNLV past Wyoming 85-70

articles.description: Khalil Ahmad had 31 points and Kyle Allman added 21 and Cal State Fullerton made five free throws down the stretch to seal a 68-66 win over UC Davis on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Cal State Fullerton holds off UC Davis for 68-66 win

videos.description: Mikal Bridges drains a corner 3-pointer as Villanova takes an early 7-0 lead over Temple.
videos.headline: Bridges 3-pointer extends Villanova's early lead

videos.description: Jalen Brunson gets the outlet pass and goes all the way down the court, showing off the moves for the layup.
videos.headline: Villanova's Brunson spin moves for bucket

videos.description: Jalen Brunson goes 3-for-5 from three on his way to 15 points in the first half.
videos.headline: Villanova's Brunson goes off for 15 points in early the first half

videos.description: Philadelphia Sixers guard Ben Simmons sits court side to watch No. 1 Villanova take on Temple.
videos.headline: Ben Simmons takes in Villanova game

videos.description: Jalen Brunson shows great hustle and steals the loose ball and Donte DiVincenzo rewards him on offense with a pass for a deep 3-pointer.
videos.headline: DiVincenzo rewards Brunson for defense

videos.description: Omari Spellman can't make up his mind, but shoots it anyway and drills a jumper.
videos.headline: Spellman sinks off-balance jumper

videos.description: Damion Moore grabs the offensive rebound and sends home an emphatic putback dunk.
videos.headline: Temple's Moore cleans up miss

videos.description: Jalen Brunson dominated the first half, going 8-for-10 from the field, including 5-for-7 from beyond the arc.
videos.headline: Brunson drops 22 points in first half

videos.description: Villanova swings the ball and finds an open Eric Paschall underneath the basket for a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Villanova ball movement leads to Paschall dunk

videos.description: Omari Spellman drains a wide open 3-pointer for his career-high 21st point of the game.
videos.headline: Spellman scores career-high 21 points

videos.description: Omari Spellman takes over the offensive load in the second half with 15 points for a career-high 25 points.
videos.headline: Spellman scores 25 points on 13 shots

videos.description: Jalen Brunson drives to the lane and beats his defender for a one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Brunson shows off athleticism with one-handed dunk

videos.description: Temple tries to apply pressure, but Phil Booth throws a lob pass to Eric Paschall for a huge dunk and a foul for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Villanova makes Temple pay for full-court press

videos.description: Vilanova coach, Jay Wright says his team "played well" in their 87-67 win over Temple, marking Nova's 11th straight win.
videos.headline: Career nights from Spellman, Brunson lead Nova victory
